# ESP32 Rainbow Website

This web application describes the ESP32 Rainbow project - a ZX Spectrum emulator based around the ESP32-S3 module. The website consists of a search engine for ZX Spectrum games that can be sent to the device along with various utility pages - a firmware update page and a file browser.

## Project Structure

- [src/main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx) - Application entry point
- [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Main application component
- [src/components/](mdc:src/components) - Reusable UI components
- [src/pages/](mdc:src/pages) - Page components for different routes
- [src/device/](mdc:src/device) - Device communication logic
- [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils) - Utility functions
- [src/context/](mdc:src/context) - React context providers
- [functions/](mdc:functions) - Cloudflare Workers serverless functions
